1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:02,110
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:02,170 --> 00:00:03,480
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,540 --> 00:00:05,240
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,010 --> 00:00:07,410
(Episode 71)

5
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:15,620
So you really are Jin Ju.

6
00:00:17,620 --> 00:00:20,330
Dr. Baek's daughter, Baek Jin Ju.

7
00:00:23,330 --> 00:00:24,330
Thank you.

8
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,770
I'm so grateful that you're alive.

9
00:00:32,070 --> 00:00:33,070
How...

10
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:35,340
did you know...

11
00:00:36,780 --> 00:00:38,240
I'm Baek Jin Ju?

12
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:48,050
(Hanbit High School
62nd Graduation Ceremony)

13
00:00:55,230 --> 00:00:56,690
You don't have to be so guarded.

14
00:00:58,060 --> 00:01:01,130
I owe a great debt to Dr. Baek.

15
00:01:03,270 --> 00:01:04,540
I'm one of the people...

16
00:01:05,340 --> 00:01:07,010
who desperately hoped
that you were still alive.

17
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:12,140
Yet, someone like that
protects Park Tae Ho?

18
00:01:13,380 --> 00:01:17,320
Even though you knew my dad
had been wrongfully killed,

19
00:01:18,580 --> 00:01:19,650
you just looked the other way?

20
00:01:24,690 --> 00:01:26,790
You have every right to resent me.

21
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:30,130
But...

22
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:32,930
there's so much you don't know.

23
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:39,940
Can you please just hear me out?

24
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:51,680
In you go.

25
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:01,760
If you wanted to save your skin,
you should've just stayed quiet.

26
00:02:02,660 --> 00:02:05,130
First, you tried
to frame Kim Myung Hui,

27
00:02:05,330 --> 00:02:07,600
and then you helped
Driver Song escape?

28
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:09,970
What are you scheming now?

29
00:02:09,970 --> 00:02:11,870
What are you talking about?

30
00:02:12,570 --> 00:02:14,970
Driver Song left
to save his own skin.

31
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:17,040
Betrayal is second nature to him.

32
00:02:18,540 --> 00:02:20,880
This just goes to show
you can't trust anyone.

33
00:02:22,410 --> 00:02:23,680
And don't dismiss my warning...

34
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:26,180
about Kim Myung Hui.
Keep a close eye on her.

35
00:02:26,990 --> 00:02:29,890
She knows everything you've done
and is just pretending not to.

36
00:02:29,990 --> 00:02:32,060
You never know
when or how she might betray you.

37
00:02:34,490 --> 00:02:36,190
Of all the nerve.

38
00:02:40,030 --> 00:02:42,170
You're the one who betrayed me,
Oh Jung Ran.

39
00:02:43,070 --> 00:02:44,540
You dared to come after my life...

40
00:02:45,070 --> 00:02:47,970
and take over my company.

41
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:51,780
Get your facts straight.
You tried to kill me first.

42
00:02:53,550 --> 00:02:57,380
After 40 years of loyalty
and devotion to you?

43
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,750
You're a monster.

44
00:03:01,420 --> 00:03:03,960
You want me to show you
what a monster I can be?

45
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:08,890
Should I make you get on your knees
and beg for my forgiveness?

46
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:14,130
Fine. Go on, just try it.

47
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:18,740
Should I kick out Hyun Jun,
that ungrateful brat?

48
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:20,170
Park Tae Ho.

49
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:23,710
Do what you want to me,
but Hyun Jun is your son.

50
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:26,610
It's not like he's my only son!

51
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:30,210
If it weren't for Chloe
and the exclusive development deal,

52
00:03:30,620 --> 00:03:32,080
I would've kicked him out already.

53
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:35,350
You seem to trust Park Min Jun
and Kim Myung Hui,

54
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:36,960
but you'll regret it.

55
00:03:37,220 --> 00:03:40,360
No. Kim Myung Hui saved my life.

56
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:44,860
I won't be fooled by anything
you say anymore, Jung Ran.

57
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:47,330
Lock her up again. Now!

58
00:03:47,730 --> 00:03:48,730
Yes, sir.

59
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:51,470
Kim Myung Hui is just using you.

60
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:55,170
She'll use you
and betray you in the end.

61
00:03:58,310 --> 00:04:01,610
I'm the one using Kim Myung Hui.

62
00:04:04,020 --> 00:04:06,750
I'll sweet-talk her
and win her over,

63
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:10,490
so that she'll protect me.

64
00:04:12,220 --> 00:04:13,930
Are you saying you were twins?

65
00:04:15,790 --> 00:04:16,790
Yes.

66
00:04:18,730 --> 00:04:19,960
I'm Kim Dan Hui...

67
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:23,330
and Kim Myung Hui
was my older sister.

68
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:28,710
She was wrongfully killed
at the hands of Oh Jung Ran.

69
00:04:32,740 --> 00:04:34,750
It's a miracle, plain and simple.

70
00:04:35,850 --> 00:04:38,480
Doctor,
your daughter is healthy too.

71
00:04:38,980 --> 00:04:43,420
Dr. Baek performed emergency surgery
and saved Min Jun.

72
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:48,290
And I was right there to deliver you
just as you were born.

73
00:04:50,030 --> 00:04:51,960
You and Min Jun.

74
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:54,930
The moment you were born
on the same day, at the same time,

75
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:57,770
was the beginning
of our intertwined fates.

76
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:04,040
So all this time since then,

77
00:05:05,110 --> 00:05:08,880
you've been living as Kim Myung Hui
just to get revenge on Oh Jung Ran?

78
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:10,750
That's right.

79
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:13,890
It's like you came back as Chloe...

80
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:16,720
to get revenge on Park Tae Ho.

81
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,830
You must've been in so much pain.

82
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:29,000
Others may not understand,

83
00:05:29,930 --> 00:05:31,200
but I do.

84
00:05:34,110 --> 00:05:37,980
The grief and guilt
of unjustly losing someone you love.

85
00:05:40,710 --> 00:05:41,980
Park Tae Ho and Choi Yu Na.

86
00:05:42,950 --> 00:05:45,480
The rage you have to endure
when facing your enemies.

87
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:48,290
Living as someone else...

88
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:51,060
and the anxiety and loneliness
that comes with it.

89
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,390
I know it hasn't been easy.

90
00:06:03,670 --> 00:06:06,640
When does it get better?

91
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:11,710
If I live through 30 years of this,

92
00:06:13,180 --> 00:06:16,710
will anything actually be better?

93
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:21,590
How did you feel when you locked...

94
00:06:21,590 --> 00:06:23,390
Oh Jung Ran in the basement
and forced her...

95
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,620
to sign the divorce papers?

96
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,490
After you get your revenge,

97
00:06:28,790 --> 00:06:30,960
does any of that anger
actually subside?

98
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,360
When I...

99
00:06:34,130 --> 00:06:35,930
take down Park Tae Ho,

100
00:06:37,340 --> 00:06:40,200
will this feeling of being trapped
in a blazing fire...

101
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:44,140
finally go away?

102
00:06:59,690 --> 00:07:00,790
Are you...

103
00:07:01,530 --> 00:07:02,960
still hurting?

104
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,600
I'm still Kim Myung Hui,

105
00:07:07,630 --> 00:07:09,630
and nothing can bring
my sister back.

106
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:13,370
So in the end,

107
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:16,640
this pain never really goes away.

108
00:07:18,010 --> 00:07:20,010
All we can do is hope that it does.

109
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:24,250
Still,

110
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:27,190
if we're together instead of alone,

111
00:07:27,650 --> 00:07:29,420
at least we won't be lonely.

112
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:34,390
When I found out
about Dr. Baek's unjust death,

113
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:36,790
I made a promise to him.

114
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,960
That after I got my revenge
on Oh Jung Ran...

115
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:45,270
and after Park Tae Ho
served his purpose, I would...

116
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:48,810
make him pay for his crimes.

117
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:52,910
Now that I've found you,

118
00:07:54,150 --> 00:07:57,520
I'll help you see your revenge
through to the end.

119
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:00,320
We have to reveal the truth
of what happened seven years ago,

120
00:08:00,590 --> 00:08:03,320
and make Park Tae Ho
and Choi Yu Na pay for their sins.

121
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:32,580
They're holding hands.

122
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:34,190
Wait.

123
00:08:35,650 --> 00:08:37,150
But she doesn't look very happy.

124
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:39,820
She's just taking it all in.

125
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:42,430
I know everything there is to know
about Dan Hui.

126
00:08:42,530 --> 00:08:43,530
I see.

127
00:08:44,630 --> 00:08:46,430
President Kim Myung Hui... No, wait.

128
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:50,770
How did Kim Dan Hui manage
to endure all those years?

129
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,610
She had someone to protect.

130
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:58,740
You're talking
about Director Park Min Jun.

131
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:01,710
Plus, having a friend like you
by her side...

132
00:09:02,180 --> 00:09:03,750
must've meant a lot to her.

133
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:09,490
Chloe, I mean Jin Ju,
had you, didn't she?

134
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:12,190
I'm sure it wasn't easy
for you either.

135
00:09:16,590 --> 00:09:18,660
Come on now.

136
00:09:18,730 --> 00:09:21,830
Why are you getting
all teary-eyed again?

137
00:09:22,070 --> 00:09:25,270
Something got in my eye, that's all.

138
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:27,670
- Oh, really? Let me see.
- What?

139
00:09:35,310 --> 00:09:37,250
Let me take a look.

140
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:42,590
Manager Kang.

141
00:09:44,060 --> 00:09:47,220
I heard Driver Song ran away.
Is that true?

142
00:09:47,290 --> 00:09:49,190
Yes, it is.

143
00:09:50,030 --> 00:09:51,960
What about my mom?

144
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:55,470
Ms. Oh Jung Ran? Oh, right.

145
00:09:56,270 --> 00:09:59,600
She'll remain in the basement.
Now, excuse me.

146
00:10:04,780 --> 00:10:06,310
He's not as respectful...

147
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:08,750
toward her anymore.

148
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:14,950
Well, at least it seems
Mom made it through okay.

149
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:22,590
This is a notice of demand
prepared by the legal team.

150
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:27,970
It voids Ms. Choi's contest win...

151
00:10:28,030 --> 00:10:30,630
and demands that she repay
her study-abroad scholarship...

152
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:32,400
and all earnings...

153
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:35,570
from her employment
because of unjust enrichment.

154
00:10:35,710 --> 00:10:39,380
The total damages claim
is one million dollars.

155
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:43,510
I will deliver this
to Choi Yu Na myself.

156
00:10:43,950 --> 00:10:45,880
- Good work.
- Thank you.

157
00:11:01,830 --> 00:11:02,900
What's this?

158
00:11:07,140 --> 00:11:08,240
(Legal Notice)

159
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:11,180
Wait, a legal notice?

160
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,950
"Claim for Damages."

161
00:11:17,580 --> 00:11:20,890
One... one million dollars?

162
00:11:21,390 --> 00:11:23,620
- For crying out loud.
- Park Min Jun.

163
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,960
This is going way too far.

164
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:29,060
Why? Compared to what you've done,

165
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:30,190
you're getting off easy.

166
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:31,200
Seriously?

167
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:33,360
You call a million dollars
getting off easy?

168
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:36,930
Even if you were born
with a silver spoon in your mouth,

169
00:11:36,930 --> 00:11:38,770
a million dollars
isn't pocket change.

170
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,310
Min Jun.

171
00:11:41,970 --> 00:11:44,140
Given our history together,
maybe you could...

172
00:11:44,140 --> 00:11:45,310
This is...

173
00:11:46,110 --> 00:11:47,110
non-negotiable.

174
00:11:47,110 --> 00:11:48,150
What?

175
00:11:49,610 --> 00:11:51,050
- This is unfair.
- Why you...

176
00:11:53,450 --> 00:11:55,190
What? You feel wronged?

177
00:11:55,950 --> 00:11:57,990
Yes, this is unfair.

178
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:01,190
Why won't you acknowledge
my hard work?

179
00:12:01,690 --> 00:12:04,230
Why do you act like
I never earned any of it?

180
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:07,160
I may have gotten help
paying for tuition,

181
00:12:07,230 --> 00:12:09,200
but I'm the one
who earned that degree.

182
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,500
It's true that I was hired at Adele
through preferential treatment,

183
00:12:11,970 --> 00:12:12,970
but I gave it my all...

184
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:15,240
and devoted myself to the company.

185
00:12:15,770 --> 00:12:16,910
What about Jin Ju?

186
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:20,280
Was what you did to her
part of your "hard work?"

187
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:24,250
- Jin Ju?
- Jin Ju?

188
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:28,450
You're unbelievable.

189
00:12:29,590 --> 00:12:31,560
If you want to argue,

190
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:33,990
do it in court.

191
00:12:36,190 --> 00:12:38,630
- For goodness' sake.
- Oh no.

192
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:40,930
Park Min Jun.

193
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:48,010
If you keep pushing me like this,
you'll force my hand.

194
00:12:48,210 --> 00:12:49,210
Force your hand?

195
00:12:49,570 --> 00:12:51,180
I'll go to the chairman
and tell him everything.

196
00:12:51,740 --> 00:12:54,480
That you know all about his crimes
and are trying to expose him.

197
00:12:54,650 --> 00:12:55,750
I'll ask him to stop you.

198
00:12:55,810 --> 00:12:59,320
Is your memory failing you too?

199
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:01,750
- What?
- Have you already forgotten...

200
00:13:01,950 --> 00:13:04,020
what my father did
back when I first learned...

201
00:13:04,590 --> 00:13:07,020
about what happened seven years ago?

202
00:13:09,130 --> 00:13:12,000
Go to my father
and tell him everything.

203
00:13:12,230 --> 00:13:15,830
I'll just tell him
that I heard the truth from you.

204
00:13:16,630 --> 00:13:18,200
Do you think...

205
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:20,870
our dear Chairman Park
will let you live...

206
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:22,640
after you've slipped up
a second time?

207
00:13:24,380 --> 00:13:28,380
- Park Min Jun...
- You have no way out now.

208
00:13:28,950 --> 00:13:32,320
Everything I lost
because of what you did...

209
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,420
seven years ago,

210
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:37,420
and all the pain I've endured.

211
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:40,260
Now it's your turn to feel it.

212
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:52,900
No.

213
00:13:53,770 --> 00:13:55,940
I'll find a way, no matter what.

214
00:13:57,140 --> 00:13:59,540
I won't let you
trample all over me...

215
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:02,580
and end my life like this.

216
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,630
It's still amazing to me.

217
00:14:21,570 --> 00:14:24,870
The baby I saw in the nursery
has grown up so much.

218
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,970
Please give her some space, okay?

219
00:14:28,070 --> 00:14:29,710
You're making her uncomfortable.

220
00:14:31,510 --> 00:14:33,810
I'm just so happy and moved
to see her.

221
00:14:34,550 --> 00:14:38,150
Seeing her again like this
really reminds me of Dr. Baek.

222
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:42,350
He was a wonderful person.

223
00:14:42,650 --> 00:14:43,720
He was.

224
00:14:44,050 --> 00:14:46,060
He was a truly wonderful person.

225
00:14:46,860 --> 00:14:50,760
He saved me when I was a mess
and got me back on my feet.

226
00:14:52,430 --> 00:14:54,630
To say he was my savior
doesn't even do him justice.

227
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:56,730
He was the same for me.

228
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:00,270
He saved my son Min Jun...

229
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:03,310
and told me that my sister
had been murdered.

230
00:15:03,970 --> 00:15:07,240
He tried so hard to help me
in any way he could.

231
00:15:08,350 --> 00:15:09,410
It's tragic...

232
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,980
how a man like that died
at the hands of Park Tae Ho.

233
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:15,990
On the day of the accident,

234
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:19,360
my dad said he'd missed
an important meeting because of me,

235
00:15:19,420 --> 00:15:22,060
and that he absolutely had
to meet that person.

236
00:15:23,330 --> 00:15:25,630
That person was you, Ms. Kim.

237
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:28,070
Not being able to meet that day...

238
00:15:28,730 --> 00:15:31,740
is why it took us so long
to get here.

239
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:37,170
Isn't it a relief
we finally found each other?

240
00:15:37,170 --> 00:15:38,180
Absolutely.

241
00:15:38,710 --> 00:15:43,510
Dr. Baek is the one
who brought us back together.

242
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:47,450
This is why I find fate
so fascinating.

243
00:15:48,050 --> 00:15:51,190
They say people who are meant to be
will always find each other again.

244
00:15:51,260 --> 00:15:53,120
Two kids who were born
on the same day, at the same time,

245
00:15:53,190 --> 00:15:55,430
met again and fell in love.

246
00:15:55,490 --> 00:15:57,060
I mean, isn't this incredible?

247
00:15:57,060 --> 00:15:58,130
It is.

248
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:00,330
Hold on. That said,

249
00:16:00,330 --> 00:16:02,500
shouldn't we tell Min Jun
right away?

250
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:07,340
You see, Min Jun missed her
more than anyone.

251
00:16:09,170 --> 00:16:10,270
Mr. Park...

252
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:14,110
already knows that she's Jin Ju.

253
00:16:18,180 --> 00:16:19,250
What...

254
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:22,750
When? How did he find out?

255
00:16:23,390 --> 00:16:25,660
You still married Park Hyun Jun...

256
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:27,520
even though Min Jun knew
who you were?

257
00:16:31,930 --> 00:16:33,000
That's why...

258
00:16:33,830 --> 00:16:37,300
he tried to stop the wedding
as soon as he regained his memory.

259
00:16:37,770 --> 00:16:39,070
Min Jun and I...

260
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:41,670
I consider us to be over.

261
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:46,780
I've already told Min Jun
to stay out of my revenge.

262
00:16:47,210 --> 00:16:52,150
Jin Ju has been blaming herself
for Min Jun being run over.

263
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:56,120
Because of that, she even married
Hyun Jun rather than Min Jun.

264
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,620
James, please.

265
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:02,260
We have to be honest with them.

266
00:17:02,990 --> 00:17:04,630
That way, there won't be
any misunderstandings.

267
00:17:04,930 --> 00:17:07,700
It doesn't change anything.

268
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:12,000
I'm going to stay in this marriage.

269
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:17,910
And I don't want you to tell Min Jun
that we know who each other is now.

270
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:20,480
All right.

271
00:17:21,580 --> 00:17:24,280
About Min Jun, and this marriage...

272
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:27,750
Let's take some time
to think about what to do.

273
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,360
Why does she care
so much about Min Jun,

274
00:17:36,860 --> 00:17:39,930
yet she's determined
to remain married to Hyun Jun?

275
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:44,100
Should I tell her
who Hyun Jun's real father is?

276
00:17:46,070 --> 00:17:48,470
You, Hyun Jun,

277
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:51,070
and also Min Jun.

278
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:54,480
I feel so sorry for all of you.

279
00:18:19,470 --> 00:18:21,910
Never mind me. You should eat.

280
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,740
It must've been rough
in the basement.

281
00:18:23,740 --> 00:18:25,440
Me? I'm fine.

282
00:18:26,610 --> 00:18:28,280
Jung Ran's the one who had it tough.

283
00:18:29,010 --> 00:18:32,050
By the way, have you checked on her?

284
00:18:32,580 --> 00:18:35,120
I think she made it through
without any major issues.

285
00:18:35,420 --> 00:18:36,850
That's a relief.

286
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:40,190
If Chloe uncovers
President Kim's weakness,

287
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:42,630
she can get out
of the basement, right?

288
00:18:43,730 --> 00:18:46,630
I'll talk to Chloe
and figure something out.

289
00:18:46,630 --> 00:18:48,300
Okay, good.

290
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:52,470
I'm so relieved
you have Chloe by your side.

291
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:55,670
I bet it feels great
to marry the woman you love...

292
00:18:55,670 --> 00:18:57,440
and live happily together.

293
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:01,010
Well...

294
00:19:02,950 --> 00:19:05,420
Being known as husband and wife...

295
00:19:06,580 --> 00:19:07,920
It feels surprisingly good.

296
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:10,590
Being by Chloe's side...

297
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:13,120
and doing things with her...

298
00:19:15,130 --> 00:19:16,930
- makes me happy.
- Of course.

299
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:21,170
Just seeing her makes you happy,

300
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:24,740
and spending time with her
is even better.

301
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:28,170
That's what true love is.

302
00:19:29,570 --> 00:19:31,110
You be good to Chloe.

303
00:19:31,110 --> 00:19:33,610
I've been treating her like royalty.

304
00:19:33,910 --> 00:19:38,620
Come on, hurry up and eat.
I have to get back to her.

305
00:19:40,580 --> 00:19:44,960
All right. Here, have some of this.
Eat up. There you go.

306
00:19:48,860 --> 00:19:50,590
- Dig in.
- Sure.

307
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:02,010
I'm sure you're aware
that Driver Song escaped.

308
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:04,840
You and Hyun Jun...

309
00:20:05,580 --> 00:20:07,680
plotted with Oh Jung Ran,
didn't you?

310
00:20:08,250 --> 00:20:09,550
What do you mean, we plotted?

311
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:12,980
Why would I help Driver Song escape
but not Mother?

312
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:15,890
That's an unfair accusation.

313
00:20:16,490 --> 00:20:18,490
How dare you call
the chairman's accusation unfair?

314
00:20:19,060 --> 00:20:21,960
Chloe, your attitude
always makes him uncomfortable.

315
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:23,760
You should leave.

316
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:25,560
Sure.

317
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:35,970
Regarding Driver Song,
I'll meet with Oh Jung Ran again.

318
00:20:36,410 --> 00:20:39,310
Given your health,
please don't worry too much.

319
00:20:40,780 --> 00:20:43,380
Now that I've appointed Min Jun
as vice president,

320
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:45,820
are you no longer angry?

321
00:20:46,950 --> 00:20:50,350
Well, it means you trust me, sir.

322
00:20:51,490 --> 00:20:52,990
Right.

323
00:20:53,690 --> 00:20:57,290
No matter what Oh Jung Ran says,
I won't doubt you,

324
00:20:58,130 --> 00:20:59,660
so you should trust me too.

325
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:03,170
They say you can't trust anyone
in this world,

326
00:21:03,230 --> 00:21:05,040
but Park Tae Ho needs someone...

327
00:21:05,570 --> 00:21:09,810
he can trust completely by his side.

328
00:21:10,540 --> 00:21:14,580
Once the divorce is finalized
and we've registered our marriage,

329
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:18,120
Myung Hui, you'll be my wife...

330
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:20,780
and the first lady of Adele Group.

331
00:21:21,990 --> 00:21:23,350
You'll be the one to protect me.

332
00:21:25,690 --> 00:21:26,690
Why?

333
00:21:27,860 --> 00:21:30,990
Don't you want to be
the woman by my side?

334
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:33,760
Of course I do.

335
00:21:34,060 --> 00:21:37,800
If you're willing to trust me,
then that's what I'll do.

336
00:21:38,170 --> 00:21:42,470
Good. Once the divorce is finalized,

337
00:21:43,610 --> 00:21:47,880
we'll register our marriage
and become husband and wife.

338
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:55,290
Park Tae Ho,

339
00:21:56,150 --> 00:21:58,790
you don't deserve
to smile like that.

340
00:21:59,760 --> 00:22:02,060
After brutally murdering Dr. Baek...

341
00:22:02,430 --> 00:22:04,060
and forcing Baek Jin Ju...

342
00:22:04,060 --> 00:22:06,660
to live every day as though
she were standing in a blazing fire,

343
00:22:07,030 --> 00:22:08,400
how could you?

344
00:22:10,370 --> 00:22:11,870
A blazing fire?

345
00:22:20,340 --> 00:22:22,010
I didn't expect them
to have a history together.

346
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:27,780
So President Kim was also living
as someone else, just like me.

347
00:22:35,530 --> 00:22:36,760
I see you got home first.

348
00:22:37,060 --> 00:22:39,460
Right. What about Driver Song?

349
00:22:39,530 --> 00:22:42,830
I got him a place to stay
and made sure he had a meal.

350
00:22:43,530 --> 00:22:47,270
Do you think that story
Driver Song told us will help us...

351
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:50,110
uncover something
about President Kim?

352
00:22:50,510 --> 00:22:52,510
Didn't you want to check it out...

353
00:22:52,510 --> 00:22:53,980
because you thought it was a clue?

354
00:22:54,110 --> 00:22:55,280
Oh, that.

355
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:58,080
I looked into it again with James,

356
00:22:58,150 --> 00:23:00,120
but I don't think
there's anything there.

357
00:23:00,250 --> 00:23:03,550
Really? I see. That's too bad.

358
00:23:04,490 --> 00:23:08,830
What was that about Dr. Baek Jun Gi
from Baek OB-GYN?

359
00:23:09,230 --> 00:23:11,360
How does he have the exact same name
as your father?

360
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:14,460
I know. I was really surprised too.

361
00:23:15,230 --> 00:23:17,930
But my dad was a businessman.

362
00:23:18,270 --> 00:23:20,570
It must just be someone
with the same name.

363
00:23:20,940 --> 00:23:24,470
Anyway,
I'll have James look into it again.

364
00:23:24,670 --> 00:23:26,480
I'll let you know
if I find anything.

365
00:23:26,540 --> 00:23:27,980
Sure. Okay, then.

366
00:23:28,410 --> 00:23:30,350
Get some rest.
I'm going to go wash up.

367
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:51,700
I'm sorry.

368
00:23:53,100 --> 00:23:55,940
I can't reveal
President Kim's secret.

369
00:23:57,610 --> 00:24:00,280
The truth will hit you differently
than it hit me.

370
00:24:08,790 --> 00:24:10,550
Meet me in the living room
of the annex.

371
00:24:20,930 --> 00:24:22,300
What's going on?

372
00:24:23,770 --> 00:24:25,270
Thinking about the accident
from seven years ago...

373
00:24:25,270 --> 00:24:26,440
reminded me of something.

374
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:28,370
I know about evidence...

375
00:24:28,370 --> 00:24:30,540
and a witness connected
to Dr. Baek's accident.

376
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:34,510
What do you mean by that?

377
00:24:35,310 --> 00:24:36,810
There was a technician...

378
00:24:38,250 --> 00:24:39,980
who planted the bomb...

379
00:24:40,650 --> 00:24:42,120
in Dr. Baek's car.

380
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:45,890
Oh Jung Ran has that information.

381
00:24:46,920 --> 00:24:50,490
What Eunhwa Trading procured
in exchange for that painting...

382
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:53,660
wasn't an object.

383
00:24:54,230 --> 00:24:55,370
It was a person.

384
00:24:55,730 --> 00:24:58,800
A device was needed
to blow up and incinerate a car.

385
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:01,870
What Park Tae Ho wanted
was a bomb maker!

386
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:06,180
I can't get that information,

387
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:09,350
but you can trick Oh Jung Ran
into giving it to you.

388
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:12,550
I'll try.
Please let me meet Oh Jung Ran.

389
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:16,290
This is the key to the basement.

390
00:25:16,550 --> 00:25:19,790
Once Mrs. Ok is asleep,
go in and see her.

391
00:25:22,590 --> 00:25:24,930
I wanted to reinvestigate
my dad's accident,

392
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:28,230
but without any evidence,
I couldn't get anywhere.

393
00:25:28,730 --> 00:25:30,030
Thanks to you,

394
00:25:30,330 --> 00:25:32,140
I think I can finally make
some progress.

395
00:25:32,570 --> 00:25:33,600
Right.

396
00:25:34,070 --> 00:25:36,710
Let's find that evidence,
no matter what.

397
00:25:44,050 --> 00:25:48,350
Song Geun Tae,
did you meet Hyun Jun or not?

398
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:50,290
And as for Chloe...

399
00:25:50,990 --> 00:25:53,260
What did she find out
about Kim Dan Hui?

400
00:25:55,730 --> 00:25:59,260
Park Tae Ho is so wrapped up in
Kim Myung Hui that he won't budge.

401
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:04,030
This is so frustrating.
I can't figure out what's going on.

402
00:26:09,540 --> 00:26:12,410
What on earth?
How did you get in here?

403
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:15,050
I stole it from Ms. Kim.

404
00:26:15,050 --> 00:26:16,810
You're talented at stealing too?

405
00:26:17,710 --> 00:26:21,320
You're the last person
I'd want as an enemy.

406
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:23,920
But we don't have much time.

407
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:28,960
Did you meet with Geun Tae?
And did you look into Kim Dan Hui?

408
00:26:29,260 --> 00:26:33,000
Yes, but I came up empty
on Kim Dan Hui.

409
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:36,900
- What?
- I think I'll change my approach.

410
00:26:37,570 --> 00:26:40,070
If I can't find Ms. Kim's weakness,

411
00:26:40,340 --> 00:26:42,770
why not use the chairman's?

412
00:26:43,170 --> 00:26:45,240
You're saying you'll go after
Park Tae Ho directly?

413
00:26:45,910 --> 00:26:49,350
The chairman seems touchy
about Temi Bio.

414
00:26:49,980 --> 00:26:51,380
There's more to the story, right?

415
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:55,250
Did he commit a crime or something?

416
00:26:57,220 --> 00:26:58,290
Well...

417
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:02,730
So there is something, isn't there?

418
00:27:03,860 --> 00:27:05,730
Then there must be evidence of it.

419
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:10,070
- Evidence?
- If there's evidence of a crime,

420
00:27:10,500 --> 00:27:12,000
I'll try to blackmail the chairman.

421
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:15,840
Evidence related to Temi Bio?

422
00:27:17,140 --> 00:27:18,610
I do know something.

423
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:20,710
Then please let me have it.

424
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:24,150
How can I trust you?

425
00:27:26,080 --> 00:27:29,150
Mother, I married Hyun Jun.

426
00:27:29,820 --> 00:27:31,960
We're already in the same boat.

427
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:35,690
If we're all in the same boat,
we'll go down together if it sinks.

428
00:27:38,430 --> 00:27:41,560
Prove to me that I can trust you.

429
00:27:42,430 --> 00:27:43,530
Prove it?

430
00:27:43,830 --> 00:27:46,640
Yes. If you get me out
of this basement,

431
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:48,470
I'll trust you.

432
00:27:50,110 --> 00:27:51,940
The Temi Bio evidence...

433
00:27:52,780 --> 00:27:54,080
will be handed over afterward.

434
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:06,060
What? She wants you to get her out
of the basement?

435
00:28:06,390 --> 00:28:09,430
I think she's testing me
to see if I'm on her side.

436
00:28:10,860 --> 00:28:14,700
She's just using this as an excuse
to get out of the basement.

437
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:16,600
What should I do?

438
00:28:17,300 --> 00:28:18,970
We went through so much trouble
to lock her in the basement,

439
00:28:19,470 --> 00:28:20,800
and now because of me...

440
00:28:22,970 --> 00:28:24,840
If this gets in the way
of your revenge,

441
00:28:25,110 --> 00:28:26,510
I'll look for another way.

442
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,280
No.

443
00:28:28,980 --> 00:28:31,080
Why take the long way around
when there's a shortcut?

444
00:28:32,150 --> 00:28:33,850
Even if we let Oh Jung Ran out,

445
00:28:34,650 --> 00:28:36,420
we just have to make sure
she's powerless.

446
00:28:36,790 --> 00:28:39,760
Still, will Chairman Park allow it?

447
00:28:40,190 --> 00:28:42,530
We have to create a situation
where he'll have no choice.

448
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:49,930
Wait. Min Jun fired Choi Yu Na?

449
00:28:51,230 --> 00:28:54,140
Over that old contest win?

450
00:28:54,700 --> 00:28:55,770
Yes.

451
00:28:56,310 --> 00:28:59,310
Why fire Choi Yu Na all of a sudden?

452
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:02,950
Didn't Ms. Choi lie to him
when he had amnesia?

453
00:29:04,510 --> 00:29:07,120
Right, she lied
that they were in love.

454
00:29:07,850 --> 00:29:10,290
So he's taking it out on her
for that?

455
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:13,890
I don't think
there's any other reason.

456
00:29:14,390 --> 00:29:16,660
Right. For now,

457
00:29:17,560 --> 00:29:20,230
- just keep an eye on things.
- Yes, understood.

458
00:29:21,870 --> 00:29:24,130
Sir, you're needed outside.

459
00:29:24,370 --> 00:29:25,870
I think there's a problem.

460
00:29:27,240 --> 00:29:28,240
A problem?

461
00:29:29,570 --> 00:29:30,670
Hello.

462
00:29:31,670 --> 00:29:32,680
So,

463
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:36,010
what brings the police to my home?

464
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:38,750
A missing person report was filed
for Oh Jung Ran.

465
00:29:39,980 --> 00:29:42,390
Is Ms. Oh not home?

466
00:29:44,290 --> 00:29:47,790
We couldn't reach her.
Why didn't her family file a report?

467
00:29:51,190 --> 00:29:53,560
Father, Mother is here.

468
00:30:02,740 --> 00:30:06,880
Mother, even if you're out of town,
you should answer your phone.

469
00:30:07,310 --> 00:30:09,210
Because no one could get
in touch with you,

470
00:30:09,210 --> 00:30:10,550
a missing person report was filed,

471
00:30:10,610 --> 00:30:12,080
causing all this commotion.

472
00:30:12,250 --> 00:30:15,220
Oh, that. I lost my phone.

473
00:30:15,350 --> 00:30:18,920
I see. Is that why you couldn't even
contact the family?

474
00:30:19,820 --> 00:30:22,630
Well, everyone knew I was on a trip.

475
00:30:23,430 --> 00:30:27,230
Besides, this trip was a lot of fun.

476
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:33,300
Anyway, I'm perfectly fine.
You can all leave now.

477
00:30:33,300 --> 00:30:35,570
Sure.
We're glad to see nothing's wrong.

478
00:30:36,210 --> 00:30:37,210
Well then.

479
00:30:44,010 --> 00:30:45,880
Right. I get it now.

480
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:48,720
This is why you helped
Driver Song escape.

481
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:51,890
You were planning to call the police
to get yourself out of trouble.

482
00:30:52,060 --> 00:30:54,490
So, what are you going to do
about it now?

483
00:30:54,990 --> 00:30:58,430
Should I go back to the basement
and let the police find me?

484
00:30:59,230 --> 00:31:03,900
Or should I go to the annex
and pretend everything is fine?

485
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:21,650
I never thought
I'd get out of there,

486
00:31:22,050 --> 00:31:23,320
but here I am.

487
00:31:23,690 --> 00:31:25,720
I'm sure this means
you trust me now.

488
00:31:26,120 --> 00:31:27,320
Of course, I do.

489
00:31:28,020 --> 00:31:31,290
You're definitely someone
I'd never want as an enemy.

490
00:31:32,130 --> 00:31:34,760
Always make sure you and I are
on the same side.

491
00:31:37,500 --> 00:31:39,100
If we're going to be
on the same side,

492
00:31:39,670 --> 00:31:42,070
you have to keep your promise,
Mother.

493
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:48,040
Please hand over the evidence...

494
00:31:49,110 --> 00:31:50,180
related to Temi Bio.

495
00:31:55,620 --> 00:31:58,420
(Head of Division 2, Park Hyun Jun)

496
00:31:59,590 --> 00:32:01,360
(Vanity)

497
00:32:01,860 --> 00:32:03,990
She must've felt uncomfortable
moving in so suddenly,

498
00:32:04,530 --> 00:32:05,560
but she didn't say a word.

499
00:32:06,860 --> 00:32:10,230
I should get her a vanity as a gift.
I wonder if this is her style.

500
00:32:15,370 --> 00:32:17,740
What is this? Why are you even here?

501
00:32:19,680 --> 00:32:21,080
I have something
to talk to you about.

502
00:32:23,850 --> 00:32:26,020
I don't think
we have anything to discuss.

503
00:32:26,280 --> 00:32:27,450
Right.

504
00:32:28,050 --> 00:32:30,490
Well, that's about to change.

505
00:32:34,490 --> 00:32:37,930
I hold your life in my hands,
you see.

506
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:40,000
What?

507
00:32:48,970 --> 00:32:50,970
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
